      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adams%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "Settlement in Adams kicked off around 1800, with David Smith erecting the first sawmill there in 1801.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        18,
        19
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adams%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "In 1804, the eastern portion of Adams was carved out to create the neighboring town of Rodman.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        20
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adams%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "During the War of 1812, Adams raised a local militia to defend its frontier homes.",
